SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS=0;

-- ── QUESTIONS ────────────────────────────────────────────────



-- (516,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian telecom company has 10 years of call records for 20 million customers. They want to use this to predict customer churn. What ethical framework should they follow?','The company must anonymise data where possible, obtain consent for new uses, apply purpose limitation under Act 843, and conduct a Data Protection Impact Assessment.',1),
-- (517,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A government uses Big Data to identify communities likely to vote against them and reduces services there. What is this called?','This is political discrimination using data — using analytics to penalise communities is unethical, undemocratic, and potentially illegal.',1),
-- (518,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A data scientist discovers that a model predicting loan defaults unfairly disadvantages rural Ghanaian women. What should they do?','The scientist has an ethical obligation to report the bias, investigate its source in the training data, and work to correct the model before deployment.',1),
-- (519,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A hospital shares patient Big Data with a pharmaceutical company for research. The data is anonymised. Why might this still pose privacy risks?','Re-identification attacks can de-anonymise data using combinations of attributes — even anonymised data can expose individuals when combined with other datasets.',1),
-- (520,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'What is the difference between correlation and causation in data analysis, and why does it matter?','Correlation means two variables move together. Causation means one causes the other. Mistaking correlation for causation leads to wrong conclusions and harmful policies.',1),
-- (521,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A blockchain network requires all nodes to agree before adding a transaction. What is this mechanism called, and what is its main drawback?','This is a consensus mechanism (e.g. Proof of Work). The main drawback is it requires significant computation, time, and energy to achieve agreement.',1),
-- (522,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A government uses blockchain for public procurement to prevent corruption. A minister tries to falsify a contract record. What happens?','Blockchain records are immutable — any attempted change to an existing record would create a hash mismatch, making the tampering immediately visible to all nodes.',1),
-- (523,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'51% of Bitcoin miners collude to control the blockchain. What attack is this and what consequence does it have?','A 51% attack means malicious actors control the majority of computing power, allowing them to reverse transactions and double-spend coins, undermining trust.',1),
-- (524,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Smart contracts execute automatically when conditions are met. A bug in a smart contract causes GHS 10 million to be sent to the wrong address. Who is liable?','Smart contract bugs are irreversible on most blockchains. Liability is unclear — this illustrates why smart contracts need rigorous auditing before deployment.',1),
-- (525,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana''s cocoa industry uses blockchain to prove fair-trade certification. A farmer bribes an inspector who enters false data. Does blockchain fix this problem?','Blockchain ensures data is not changed after entry but cannot verify the truthfulness of data at the point of entry — the "garbage in, garbage out" problem still applies.',1),
-- (526,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An autonomous vehicle in Accra must choose between hitting one pedestrian or swerving and injuring its passenger. How should it be programmed?','This is the trolley problem applied to AI ethics. There is no universally agreed solution — different ethical frameworks (utilitarian vs deontological) suggest different responses.',1),
-- (527,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana plans to deploy agricultural robots to harvest cocoa. 2 million farmers currently do this by hand. Analyse the societal impact.','Robots increase efficiency and reduce physical labour but displace millions of farm workers, requiring massive reskilling programmes and social safety nets.',1),
-- (528,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A military drone can identify and attack targets autonomously without human approval. What ethical framework governs its use?','Lethal Autonomous Weapons Systems (LAWS) are highly controversial — international humanitarian law requires meaningful human control over life-or-death decisions.',1),
-- (529,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A robot care assistant in a Ghanaian elderly care home monitors residents 24/7. What privacy and dignity concerns arise?','Continuous monitoring violates residents'' right to privacy. Balancing safety monitoring with dignity requires careful policy design and resident consent.',1),
-- (530,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A school robotics team''s robot fails in a competition because of a software bug. Analyse how the engineering design process should have prevented this.','Systematic testing, debugging, and iteration in the engineering design process should have identified software issues before competition through multiple test runs.',1),
-- (531,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Someone downloads and 3D prints a functioning firearm. What legal, ethical, and safety issues does this raise?','3D-printed firearms bypass gun control laws, create unregistered and undetectable weapons, and raise serious public safety concerns requiring regulation.',1),
-- (532,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A pharmaceutical company 3D prints personalised drug dosages for patients. What regulatory challenges does this present?','Personalised 3D-printed medicines require individual quality control for each dose, creating enormous regulatory challenges for approvals and liability.',1),
-- (533,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Intellectual property: A designer in Ghana creates an original 3D model. Someone downloads it and prints thousands to sell. What right is violated and what can the designer do?','Copyright and intellectual property rights are violated. The designer can DMCA takedown the file, register the design as IP, and pursue legal action.',1),
-- (534,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Space agencies use 3D printing to manufacture parts on the International Space Station. Why is this significant for space exploration?','Manufacturing in space eliminates the cost and time of launching replacement parts from Earth, enabling longer missions and faster repairs in orbit.',1),
-- (535,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A 3D-printed bridge fails in Ghana because the engineer used the wrong material specifications. What principles of engineering ethics were violated?','The engineer violated professional duty of care, the obligation to ensure public safety, and failed to apply appropriate material standards.',1),
-- (536,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'MTN Ghana''s MoMo system goes offline for 6 hours. Millions of Ghanaians cannot access money. Analyse the systemic risk.','Ghana''s heavy dependence on a single MoMo provider creates systemic financial risk — outages affect millions simultaneously, highlighting the need for regulatory backup systems.',1),
-- (537,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A fintech company uses AI to offer higher interest loans to Ghanaians in low-income areas. How does this compare to historical financial discrimination?','AI-driven predatory lending replicates redlining — using data proxies (location, transaction patterns) to charge higher rates to disadvantaged groups.',1),
-- (538,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana''s e-Cedi is a Central Bank Digital Currency. How is it different from Bitcoin, and what advantages does it offer Ghana?','e-Cedi is government-issued and regulated (stable value). Bitcoin is decentralised and volatile. e-Cedi offers financial inclusion while maintaining monetary policy control.',1),
-- (539,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A hacker SIM-swaps a Ghanaian businessman''s number and empties his MoMo account. Analyse the security failure.','SIM-swap fraud exploits weak telecom identity verification. Failures include inadequate KYC, lack of SIM-change notifications, and no transaction delay for new SIMs.',1),
-- (540,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A fintech startup offers 20% monthly returns to investors using a blockchain-based platform. What warning signs indicate this is a scam?','20% monthly returns (240% annually) are impossible in legitimate investments. This is a Ponzi scheme — blockchain branding makes scams appear legitimate.',1),
-- (541,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A student becomes addicted to VR gaming, spending 10 hours daily in virtual environments. Analyse the psychological and physical impacts.','VR addiction causes social isolation, neglect of real-world relationships, eye strain, and dissociation between virtual and real environments.',1),
-- (542,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AR system in a Ghanaian hospital overlays surgical guidance on a patient during an operation. The AR system fails mid-procedure. Analyse the risk.','Critical AR failure mid-surgery could confuse the surgeon, cause spatial disorientation, and require immediate fallback to traditional methods — backup protocols are essential.',1),
-- (543,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'The metaverse allows people to create virtual identities. Analyse the implications for privacy, identity, and Ghanaian cultural values.','Virtual identities enable anonymity (privacy benefit) but also fraud, impersonation, and separation from cultural norms and accountability.',1),
-- (544,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A company creates a VR simulation that accurately recreates a traumatic event. A trauma survivor is exposed to it unknowingly. What harm occurs?','Unexpected VR exposure to traumatic content can cause or worsen PTSD. Ethical VR design requires trigger warnings, consent, and content classification.',1),
-- (545,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AR app used by police overlays criminal record data on pedestrians'' faces in real time. Analyse the civil liberties implications.','This is a mass surveillance system violating presumption of innocence, right to privacy, and free movement — raising profound civil liberties concerns.',1),
-- (546,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI system predicts that 15% of students in a Ghanaian school will fail WASSCE. Teachers use this to stop giving extra help to predicted-failing students. What ethical problem occurs?','A self-fulfilling prophecy — the AI prediction causes the outcome it predicted by changing teacher behaviour, making the AI causal rather than predictive.',1),
-- (547,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A manufacturer stores all IoT device data in one central server. What single point of failure risk does this create?','If the central server is compromised or fails, all IoT device data is lost or exposed simultaneously — decentralised or distributed storage reduces this risk.',1),
-- (548,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A government stores election data exclusively in a private cloud. Opposition parties demand transparency. What architecture would address both security and transparency?','A hybrid model using private cloud for sensitive data with public blockchain-verified hashes for transparency allows security without compromising auditability.',1),
-- (549,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A researcher uses social media scraping to collect data about Ghanaian users without consent for a study on political opinion. What ethical violations occur?','This violates informed consent, purpose limitation, and data minimisation principles under ethical research guidelines and data protection law.',1),
-- (550,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana has one of Africa''s highest mobile money adoption rates. Analyse THREE factors that enabled this success.','Success factors include high mobile phone penetration, large unbanked population needing financial services, GhIPSS interoperability infrastructure, Bank of Ghana supportive regulation, and Zipline/startup ecosystem.',1),
-- (551,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A robot designed to care for elderly patients in Ghana must navigate cultural norms around respect for elders. What design considerations are needed?','The robot must use respectful language in local languages, avoid physical contact norms, defer to family decisions, and incorporate Ghanaian social protocols.',1),
-- (552,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI tutoring system gives students immediate feedback. Research shows students learn better with immediate feedback. However, struggling students stop trying and just ask the AI. What pedagogical problem does this create?','Over-reliance on AI reduces productive struggle — students need to develop resilience and problem-solving skills through challenges.',1),
-- (553,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian cooperative uses a private blockchain to track member savings. After 2 years, only 3 members know how to maintain the system. Analyse the sustainability risk.','Concentration of technical knowledge in few people creates a single point of failure — if those members leave, the system cannot be maintained.',1),
-- (554,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Construction companies in Ghana consider 3D printing concrete homes. Analyse the economic and social impact on the construction industry.','3D-printed housing reduces labour costs and construction time but displaces construction workers. Benefits include lower housing costs and faster delivery for Ghana\'s housing deficit.',1),
-- (555,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A VR education company claims their product improves learning outcomes by 40%. Evaluate the strength of this claim.','Marketing claims require peer-reviewed evidence, large sample sizes, controlled studies, and consideration of which subjects and age groups benefit — scepticism is warranted.',1),
-- (556,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Countries are competing to be AI leaders. Ghana has limited computing infrastructure and AI expertise. What strategy could Ghana adopt?','Ghana should focus on AI applications solving local problems (agriculture, health), build AI talent through education, leverage cloud computing, and participate in African AI initiatives.',1),
-- (557,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A school deploys IoT cameras in every classroom for security. Teachers feel constantly monitored. Analyse the workplace privacy issue.','Surveillance of employees without clear purpose, limits, and transparent policy violates workplace privacy rights and damages staff trust and morale.',1),
-- (558,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian company uses cloud AI services from a US company. The AI makes discriminatory decisions against Ghanaian users. Who is accountable?','Accountability is complex — the Ghanaian company deploying the AI is responsible, the US provider shares responsibility for the AI design. Both must ensure non-discrimination.',1),
-- (559,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Data brokers sell personal data of Ghanaian citizens collected from various apps. Most users are unaware. What regulatory response is needed?','Ghana must enforce Act 843 vigorously, require data broker registration, mandate opt-out mechanisms, and increase public awareness of data rights.',1),
-- (560,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Mobile money agents in Ghana sometimes charge extra fees beyond official rates. Analyse why this happens and what can be done.','Agents in areas with few competitors have market power to charge extra. Solutions include more agents per area, transparent fee display regulations, and consumer reporting mechanisms.',1),
-- (561,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian mine uses autonomous robots instead of human miners. Analyse the economic impact on the local community.','While robots improve safety and efficiency, they displace miners who support local economies — mines must invest in community transition programmes.',1),
-- (562,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI system is used to allocate scarce dialysis machines in a Ghanaian hospital. It consistently deprioritises elderly patients. Analyse the ethical issue.','Age-based deprioritisation may violate non-discrimination principles. AI should use clinically justified criteria only and be subject to human ethical oversight.',1),
-- (563,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A consortium of African central banks wants to create a blockchain-based pan-African payment system. What technical and political challenges would they face?','Technical: interoperability of different blockchains, scalability. Political: monetary sovereignty, regulatory harmonisation, and trust between nations.',1),
-- (564,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A student downloads and 3D prints a model of the Golden Stool of the Ashanti. What cultural and ethical considerations arise?','The Golden Stool is a sacred Ashanti symbol. Reproducing it trivialises cultural heritage, potentially disrespects traditions, and may violate cultural property protections.',1),
-- (565,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A country uses VR propaganda to make citizens emotionally experience events that never happened. Analyse the danger.','VR propaganda exploits the immersive emotional power of VR to create false memories and manipulate public opinion beyond what text or video can achieve.',1),
-- (566,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A smart grid in Ghana uses IoT to balance electricity supply. A cyberattack shuts it down during a heatwave. Analyse the cascading effects.','Grid failure causes: hospital equipment failure, food spoilage, economic activity halt, water pump failure, and potentially deaths — critical infrastructure attacks are acts of war.',1),
-- (567,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A university stores all research data on a cloud service that shuts down unexpectedly. What data governance failure occurred?','The university failed to maintain backups, understand data portability rights in the SLA, and plan for provider failure — data governance requires exit strategies.',1),
-- (568,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A study finds high mobile data usage correlates with higher income in Ghana. Is it safe to use this to deny loans to low-data users?','No — this would create a discriminatory proxy for income. Low data usage may reflect cost barriers, not financial risk. The variable is confounded.',1),
-- (569,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian government proposes making all transactions above GHS 100 digital-only. Analyse the impact on different population groups.','Digital-only payments exclude the elderly, rural poor, and those without smartphones. It could reduce corruption but must include transitional support.',1),
-- (570,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'WAEC uses AI to mark WASSCE essays. Some markers are made redundant. Analyse whether this is justified from multiple perspectives.','From efficiency: AI marking is faster and cheaper. From fairness: AI cannot assess nuanced writing. From employment: redundancy harms workers. Solution: AI-assisted human marking.',1),
-- (571,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI system correctly predicts rain will fall in a specific Ghanaian village 80% of the time. A farmer trusts it completely and stops observing the sky. What risk does this pose?','Over-reliance on AI predictions without human judgement is dangerous — the 20% error rate can cause crop failure if the farmer ignores direct environmental observations.',1),
-- (572,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian startup claims their product is "on the blockchain" but stores data in a regular database. What is this called and what harm does it cause?','This is blockchain-washing — using blockchain terminology to appear innovative without the actual benefits. It misleads investors and regulators.',1),
-- (573,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A pharmaceutical company 3D prints counterfeit drugs in Ghana. How could blockchain and 3D printing work together to solve this?','Blockchain can verify authentic drug batch records; 3D printing with embedded digital watermarks can prove manufacturing origin and authenticity.',1),
-- (574,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AR app translates written Ghanaian languages (Twi, Ga, Ewe) in real time through a phone camera. What impact could this have on language preservation?','Real-time translation makes minority languages more accessible and useful, potentially encouraging use. However, it may also reduce motivation to learn languages formally.',1),
-- (575,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'IoT health monitors send data every second from 100,000 patients. Doctors cannot review all data. How does AI solve this and what new problem does it create?','AI filters and alerts on critical patterns. New problem: if the AI misclassifies a critical reading, it may be missed entirely — false negatives in healthcare are dangerous.',1),
-- (576,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Calculate the annual cost if a Ghanaian company uses a cloud service at $0.023 per GB stored and they have 50TB of data.','50TB = 50,000 GB. 50,000 × $0.023 = $1,150/month. Annual cost = $1,150 × 12 = $13,800 per year — plus data transfer and compute costs.',1),
-- (577,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A school tracks every click, keystroke, and pause of students using an e-learning platform. Teachers get a detailed behavioural profile. Analyse the educational and ethical implications.','Detailed tracking enables personalised learning but creates surveillance anxiety, may deter experimentation, and raises serious data minimisation and children''s privacy concerns.',1),
-- (578,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Tigo Cash exits Ghana''s mobile money market. Millions of Tigo Cash users cannot access their money for weeks. What regulation should have prevented this?','Regulators should require mobile money providers to maintain an escrow fund, have an exit plan protecting user funds, and transfer accounts to another provider seamlessly.',1),
-- (579,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A robot programmed to remove invasive plants from Ghana''s forests cannot distinguish invasive from native species accurately. Analyse the environmental risk.','Incorrectly removing native plant species could damage ecosystems, destroy biodiversity, and cause irreversible ecological harm.',1),
-- (580,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'AI-generated deepfake videos of Ghanaian politicians saying things they never said go viral before an election. Analyse the threat to democracy.','Deepfakes undermine trust in authentic media, manipulate voters with false information, and can swing elections — detection technology and media literacy are urgent countermeasures.',1),
-- (581,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana''s first smart building uses IoT to control access, temperature, and power. The building management system is compromised. Analyse what attackers could do.','Attackers could lock or unlock doors, disable fire systems, adjust temperature to dangerous levels, steal occupancy data, and disrupt building services.',1),
-- (582,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A hospital uses cloud computing for medical imaging AI. The internet connection fails during an emergency. Analyse the impact.','Without cloud connectivity, the AI imaging analysis is unavailable. Hospitals need offline fallback procedures and edge computing for time-critical medical systems.',1),
-- (583,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A university research team discovers that Ghanaian social media users can be identified 87% of the time from "anonymised" data using just three attributes. What does this reveal?','True anonymisation of Big Data is nearly impossible — re-identification risk is high, making "anonymised" data still personally identifiable and subject to data protection laws.',1),
-- (584,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana adopts blockchain voting. A technical expert discovers a vulnerability but is told to keep quiet to avoid panic. What should the expert do?','The expert has a professional and ethical obligation to report the vulnerability through proper channels — concealing security risks endangers the entire election.',1),
-- (585,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian school invests GHS 50,000 in 3D printers but lacks filament supply, technical support, and teacher training. After 1 year they are unused. What went wrong?','Technology adoption requires ecosystem support — hardware alone is insufficient without consumables supply chains, maintenance, training, and curriculum integration.',1),
-- (586,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A VR platform collects detailed biometric data (eye movement, heart rate, emotional responses) from users. Analyse the data privacy implications.','Biometric data is the most sensitive personal data category. VR platforms collecting it without clear consent, security, and purpose limitation poses extreme privacy risks.',1),
-- (587,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian diaspora sends remittances home via a blockchain platform charging 1% versus banks charging 8%. Analyse the economic impact on Ghana.','Reducing remittance costs from 8% to 1% saves families significant money — Ghana receives billions in remittances, so even 1% savings represents enormous aggregate economic benefit.',1),
-- (588,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian tech company wants to build Ghana''s first humanoid robot assistant for hospitals. List the top 5 technical, cultural, and regulatory challenges.','Technical: navigation, NLP for local languages. Cultural: patient comfort with robots, gender norms. Regulatory: liability for robot errors, medical device certification.',1),
-- (589,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI weather prediction system trained on 50 years of weather data fails to predict a new type of extreme rainfall event in Ghana. Why?','AI cannot predict events outside its training distribution. Climate change creates new weather patterns not present in historical data, making AI models less reliable.',1),
-- (590,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana''s land registry currently has millions of disputed records. A blockchain system is proposed. What is the fundamental challenge of migrating existing disputed records?','Blockchain preserves records permanently — if disputed or corrupt records are migrated, those errors become immutable. Resolving disputes before migration is essential.',1),
-- (591,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian company is fined for a data breach that exposed customer records stored in the cloud. The breach was the cloud provider''s fault. Who is ultimately responsible?','The company deploying the cloud is legally responsible to their customers. They can pursue the cloud provider separately. Responsibility does not transfer with cloud migration.',1),
-- (592,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An algorithm denies insurance to residents in certain Accra neighbourhoods based on postcode. How is this discriminatory even if race is not a variable?','Postcode acts as a proxy for race and socioeconomic status — this is indirect discrimination, illegal even when protected characteristics are not explicitly used.',1),
-- (593,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Farmers in northern Ghana use solar-powered IoT sensors. The sensors work but farmers lack smartphones to view data. Analyse the digital divide issue.','Technology adoption requires the full ecosystem including devices, connectivity, literacy, and training — hardware deployment without access to data is worthless.',1),
-- (594,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A museum in Accra uses VR to recreate historical slavery routes. Some visitors find it deeply disturbing. Analyse the ethical responsibility of the curators.','Curators must: provide trigger warnings, offer alternative experiences, ensure historical accuracy, consult affected communities, and have support resources available.',1),
-- (595,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI robot judges a Ghanaian beauty pageant, replacing human judges. Analyse whether this is appropriate.','Beauty pageants involve subjective cultural, social, and aesthetic judgements that AI cannot make legitimately. AI lacks cultural competence, empathy, and community legitimacy.',1),
-- (596,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI system refuses to answer questions about Ghanaian traditional medicine, classifying all traditional remedies as "misinformation." What problem does this reveal?','The AI has been trained on Western-centric medical data and lacks knowledge of validated traditional medicine, showing cultural bias in AI knowledge systems.',1),
-- (597,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Cryptocurrency promoters target Ghanaian youth with promises of 100% returns monthly. Analyse why young people are particularly vulnerable.','Young people may lack financial literacy, trust social media influencers, fear missing out (FOMO), and lack assets to lose — making them targets for crypto scams.',1),
-- (598,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian NGO uses a public blockchain to publish aid distribution records so donors can verify their money reached beneficiaries. What are the benefits and risks?','Benefits: donor transparency, reduced corruption. Risks: beneficiary privacy exposure if records are too detailed, and public records may be exploited by bad actors.',1),
-- (599,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A student 3D prints and sells replicas of KNUST\'s logo merchandise. Analyse the intellectual property implications.','KNUST\'s logo is registered intellectual property. Reproducing and selling it without authorisation infringes trademark rights and is commercially illegal.',1),
-- (600,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian city becomes entirely dependent on IoT infrastructure for water, power, and traffic. A massive IoT failure occurs simultaneously. Analyse the cascading crisis.','Simultaneous failure of water, power, and traffic systems causes cascading crises: hospitals fail, roads become gridlocked, water supply stops — demonstrating the danger of total digital infrastructure dependence.',1),
-- (601,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian AI startup wants to build a large language model like ChatGPT but in Twi. What data challenges would they face?','Twi has limited digitised text compared to English. The team needs to collect, clean, and annotate large amounts of Twi text — a massive and expensive undertaking.',1),
-- (602,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana''s government uses a single cloud provider for all government services. The provider increases prices by 300% after 3 years. What is this called?','This is vendor lock-in — dependency on one provider gives them pricing power. Governments should use open standards and multi-cloud strategies to maintain bargaining power.',1),
-- (603,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian public health agency wants to map disease spread using mobile phone location data. People have not consented. Is this justified?','Public health emergencies may justify temporary, proportionate use of location data with independent oversight, sunset clauses, and anonymisation — but not permanent or commercial use.',1),
-- (604,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An autonomous robot security guard in Accra detains a person based on AI facial recognition. The person is innocent. What rights have been violated?','Liberty (unlawful detention), right to be presumed innocent, and protection from algorithmic discrimination — all violated by acting on unverified AI identification.',1),
-- (605,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian bank uses AI credit scoring that disadvantages women entrepreneurs because historical loan data reflects past discrimination. How can this bias be corrected?','Remove discriminatory historical data, use alternative data sources, apply fairness constraints in the model, and conduct regular bias audits with diverse teams.',1),
-- (606,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An e-learning company sells VR headsets to Ghanaian schools. The headsets collect student data including eye-tracking. What COPPA equivalent protection applies in Ghana?','Ghana\'s Data Protection Act 2012 protects all persons. Children\'s data requires special care — explicit parental consent and strict data minimisation must be applied.',1),
-- (607,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A government issues digital identity on a blockchain. If a citizen\'s private key is stolen, what happens and how is this different from a traditional ID?','A stolen blockchain private key permanently transfers control of the digital identity — unlike a physical ID that can be cancelled and reissued. Key management is a critical challenge.',1),
-- (608,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana has scarce medical resources. 3D-printed medical devices could save lives but are not certified. Should they be used in emergencies?','Emergency use of unvalidated devices raises safety risks. A framework for emergency authorisation with informed patient consent and post-use reporting should be developed.',1),
-- (609,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI system trained to identify "violence" in social media posts consistently flags images of traditional Ghanaian wrestling. What does this illustrate?','The AI lacks cultural context — behaviour normalised in one culture may appear violent to an AI trained on Western data, causing systematic misclassification.',1),
-- (610,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana plans to give all citizens a national IoT identity chip. Citizens refuse citing religious and privacy concerns. Analyse the competing interests.','Government interest in security and efficiency competes with bodily autonomy, religious beliefs about bodily modification, and privacy rights — coercive implementation is not justified.',1),
-- (611,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A cloud-based e-learning platform used by 500,000 Ghanaian students goes offline during WASSCE mock examinations. Analyse the impact and prevention.','Mass exam disruption affects student assessment fairness. Prevention: offline mode for critical periods, SLA guarantees, government-operated backup, and exam scheduling away from maintenance windows.',1),
-- (612,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian insurance company uses social media analysis to increase premiums for people who post about risky hobbies. Is this ethical?','Using public social media data for insurance pricing without consent raises fairness, discrimination, and chilling effect concerns — people may stop sharing content freely.',1),
-- (613,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A robot farmer in Ghana harvests 10 times more crops per day than a human farm worker but the robot breaks down frequently requiring expensive repairs. Analyse the true cost.','Total cost of ownership must include downtime, repairs, parts, technical expertise, and initial cost — efficiency gains may not outweigh total costs without good maintenance infrastructure.',1),
-- (614,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A study shows that Ghanaian rural women use MoMo primarily for saving, not sending. How should fintech companies respond to this insight?','Companies should design products specifically for the savings behaviour of rural women: higher interest mobile savings accounts, Susu group savings features, and targeted financial literacy.',1),
-- (615,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian cultural festival uses VR to allow global Ghanaians in the diaspora to participate virtually. Analyse the cultural and technological implications.','VR diaspora participation preserves cultural connections and expands audience but cannot fully replicate physical community experience, food, touch, and real-time social interaction.',1),
-- (616,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Governments worldwide debate whether to regulate AI. Ghana''s Parliament is considering an AI Act. What THREE key provisions should it include?','Key provisions: mandatory impact assessments for high-risk AI; prohibition of autonomous lethal AI; transparency requirements; anti-discrimination audits; and data protection compliance.',1),
-- (617,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana''s electoral commission considers putting votes on a public blockchain for transparency. Critics say this violates ballot secrecy. Analyse both sides.','Transparency argument: public verification prevents fraud. Secrecy argument: linking votes to public addresses could allow vote-buying verification — a zero-knowledge proof approach could address both.',1),
-- (618,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian architect designs affordable housing using 3D-printed concrete. The design is beautiful but uses 30% more material than traditional methods. What trade-off analysis is needed?','Compare: material cost increase vs labour savings; environmental impact of more concrete vs reduced transport; speed of construction vs material waste; affordability vs sustainability.',1),
-- (619,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian school installs IoT devices that monitor student attention levels using cameras and AI. Parents are not informed. What institutional failures occurred?','Failure of transparency, duty of care, informed consent, and data governance. Schools must publish policies, obtain parental consent, and give students the right to opt out.',1),
-- (620,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian bank stores backups in a data centre 5km away. An earthquake damages both the main data centre and the backup. What principle of disaster recovery was violated?','Geographic separation — backups must be stored far enough apart that a single disaster cannot destroy both. Best practice uses geographically separate regions.',1),
-- (621,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An algorithm trained on Ghanaian criminal conviction data recommends longer sentences for defendants from certain regions. What legal and ethical challenge does this create?','Regional discrimination in sentencing violates equal protection under the law. The algorithm perpetuates historical discrimination — courts cannot delegate sentencing to AI.',1),
-- (622,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A hospital robot administers the wrong drug dosage due to a calibration error. Who is liable — the hospital, the robot manufacturer, or the doctor?','Liability is shared: manufacturer (if design flaw), hospital (if maintenance failures), and doctor (if override was possible but not used). Clear liability frameworks for medical robots are urgently needed.',1),
-- (623,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana''s fintech industry is mostly dominated by South African and international companies. Analyse the economic implications and policy responses.','Foreign dominance means profits leave Ghana. Policy responses: local ownership requirements, Ghanaian startup support funds, API access requirements, and preference for locally-developed solutions.',1),
-- (624,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A pharmaceutical company uses VR experiences to market drugs to doctors, creating strong emotional associations. Analyse the ethical concern.','Using VR\'s emotional power to influence medical prescribing decisions bypasses rational decision-making and may compromise the independence of medical judgement.',1),
-- (625,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana invests in a national AI programme but most AI talent immediately emigrates to the USA. Analyse this brain drain and possible solutions.','Solutions include competitive salaries in Ghana, diaspora engagement programmes, research funding, remote work opportunities with global firms, and creating a local AI startup ecosystem.',1),
-- (626,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian diaspora association manages millions of dollars in remittances through a DAO (Decentralised Autonomous Organisation). A code exploit drains all funds. What legal recourse exists?','DAOs often have unclear legal status — funds may be unrecoverable with no clear entity to sue. This illustrates the urgent need for legal frameworks governing DAOs.',1),
-- (627,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A researcher proposes using 3D bioprinting to create organs for transplant in Ghana where organ donation is rare due to cultural beliefs. Analyse the ethical and cultural dimensions.','The technology offers life-saving potential but must navigate Ghanaian cultural and religious beliefs about the body. Community engagement and religious leader consultation are essential.',1),
-- (628,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An IoT water management system in a Ghanaian community charges per litre usage tracked automatically. Poor families cannot afford enough water. Analyse the equity issue.','Metered IoT water systems may improve efficiency but create equity problems — water is a human right. Progressive pricing, subsidies for the poor, and free minimum allocations are needed.',1),
-- (629,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse why cloud computing has enabled small Ghanaian startups to compete with larger companies.','Cloud provides startups with enterprise-grade computing, storage, and AI services on a pay-as-you-go basis — eliminating the need for large capital investment in infrastructure.',1),
-- (630,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A journalist uses Big Data analysis to expose corruption in Ghana\'s procurement system. The government tries to access the journalist\'s data sources. Analyse the press freedom issue.','Compelled source disclosure chills investigative journalism. Press freedom protections and shield laws must prevent governments from using data access to identify and intimidate sources.',1),
-- (631,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana\'s National Robotics Competition produces talented student roboticists. Most win scholarships abroad. Analyse how Ghana can retain this talent.','Retention strategies: Ghanaian robotics industry investment, government contracts for local robotics firms, competitive researcher salaries, and national innovation challenges with meaningful prizes.',1),
-- (632,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian MoMo user sends money to the wrong number. The recipient refuses to return it. What regulatory protection should exist?','Fintech regulation should mandate reversal mechanisms for accidental transfers, require recipient verification before sending, and provide dispute resolution through the Bank of Ghana.',1),
-- (633,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian company develops an AR app to help tourists learn about cultural heritage sites. The app monetises by selling user location data to advertisers. Analyse the ethical issue.','Using tourist location data for advertising without disclosure exploits users who expected an educational cultural experience — this is a deceptive data practice.',1),
-- (634,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI writes news articles about Ghana\'s parliament faster than human journalists. Analyse the impact on journalism.','AI-written news reduces costs and speed but lacks contextual understanding, investigative capability, source relationships, and the ability to report on complex political nuances.',1),
-- (635,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A private company owns the blockchain infrastructure used for Ghana\'s land registry. Analyse the governance risk.','Private control of public records creates conflicts of interest — the company could hold government to ransom, change fees, or fail. Public infrastructure should be publicly governed.',1),
-- (636,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A 3D-printed COVID-19 face shield prototype is produced in 2 hours during a supply shortage in Ghana. What does this demonstrate about 3D printing in emergencies?','3D printing enables rapid local manufacturing of emergency equipment during supply chain disruptions — reducing dependence on international supply and saving lives.',1),
-- (637,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An IoT energy management system in a Ghanaian office building reduces energy consumption by 35%. Calculate annual savings if the electricity bill was GHS 120,000 per year.','35% of GHS 120,000 = GHS 42,000 saved per year. If the IoT system cost GHS 80,000 to install, it pays back in under 2 years.',1),
-- (638,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian e-government portal crashes every time citizens rush to renew licences before the deadline. What cloud architecture solves this?','Auto-scaling cloud architecture automatically adds server capacity during peak demand and reduces it when demand drops, eliminating deadline-driven crashes.',1),
-- (639,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian telecom company analyses call patterns to identify which subscribers are likely to switch to a competitor (churn prediction). What actions should they take?','Proactive retention: targeted offers to at-risk customers, improved service, loyalty rewards, and personalised communication before the customer decides to leave.',1),
-- (640,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An autonomous robot security system at a Ghanaian airport uses facial recognition to flag persons of interest. Analyse the accuracy requirements and consequences of errors.','Airport security requires extremely high accuracy — false positives (wrongly flagging innocents) cause distress and discrimination; false negatives (missing actual threats) create security risks.',1),
-- (641,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'GhIPSS processes millions of instant payment transactions daily. Analyse what would happen if the system experienced a cyberattack during the Christmas shopping period.','Attack during peak period maximises disruption — millions of transactions fail, businesses lose revenue, customers cannot pay, and confidence in digital payments collapses.',1),
-- (642,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian politician uses deepfake AR technology to appear to speak at political rallies they did not attend. Analyse the threat to electoral integrity.','AI-generated fake appearances violate campaign laws, manipulate voters with false presence, and undermine trust in authentic political communication.',1),
-- (643,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI model trained to detect fake news in English performs poorly on Ghanaian English and pidgin. What does this reveal about AI development?','AI systems developed without diverse linguistic and cultural training data perform poorly in underrepresented contexts — global AI must incorporate African languages and contexts.',1),
-- (644,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian student uses a decentralised platform to take out a crypto loan using digital assets as collateral. The crypto value drops 80%. What happens?','If collateral value falls below the loan threshold, the smart contract automatically liquidates the collateral — the student loses their assets. This is crypto margin call risk.',1),
-- (645,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian fashion designer uses 3D printing to produce unique accessories. How could they use blockchain and 3D printing together to create a sustainable business model?','Blockchain verifies design authenticity; 3D printing allows on-demand local production eliminating inventory costs — the designer can sell verified digital files globally.',1),
-- (646,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An IoT fleet management system shows that government vehicles travel privately during working hours. Officials deny it. How does IoT data resolve this dispute?','IoT GPS data with timestamps provides objective, tamper-resistant evidence of vehicle locations — ending he-said-she-said disputes with verifiable facts.',1),
-- (647,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian cloud startup offers cheaper prices than AWS. It lacks data centres in Ghana and routes all data through Singapore. What concern should Ghanaian customers have?','Data leaving Ghana to Singapore is subject to Singapore and potentially US jurisdiction — customers need to know where data physically resides and which laws apply.',1),
-- (648,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Researchers find that Ghana\'s maternal mortality correlates with distance to healthcare facilities. How should policymakers respond to this data insight?','Policymakers should use this evidence to prioritise mobile clinics, telemedicine expansion, and healthcare facility construction in high-distance high-mortality areas.',1),
-- (649,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian university wants to develop a robot that can speak and understand Akan languages. What NLP challenges make this technically difficult?','Akan is a tonal, agglutinative language with limited digitised training data, multiple dialects, and scarce NLP research — requiring extensive original language resource development.',1),
-- (650,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse how Ghana\'s MoMo ecosystem could be the foundation for a broader digital economy including healthcare, education, and government services.','MoMo provides a trusted, widely adopted digital payment layer that can be extended: health insurance premiums, school fees, government service fees, and merchant payments — creating an integrated digital ecosystem.',1),
-- (651,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian court uses an AI system to calculate bail amounts. Defendants from Nima receive higher bail than those from East Legon for the same offence. What must happen?','The system must be suspended, audited for bias, and the discriminatory decisions reviewed. AI should not be used for consequential legal decisions without human oversight and bias testing.',1),
-- (652,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana adopts a national digital identity system on blockchain. Citizens who lack smartphones cannot register. Analyse the digital exclusion problem.','Digital identity systems must provide alternative access (agents, community centres, offline cards) to avoid excluding the elderly, rural, and low-income citizens from essential services.',1),
-- (653,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A 3D printing company in Accra wants to manufacture medical equipment for export. What international standards must they meet?','Medical device manufacturers must comply with ISO 13485 (quality management), FDA or CE marking (for US/EU markets), and Ghana FDA registration for domestic use.',1),
-- (654,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse whether Ghana is ready for a large-scale IoT deployment across its cities, considering infrastructure, skills, and governance.','Readiness assessment: improving 4G coverage but rural gaps exist; limited IoT engineering talent; weak cybersecurity governance; improving electricity but outages remain — readiness is partial.',1),
-- (655,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian NGO uses free cloud services for 5 years then the provider discontinues the free tier. What lesson in cloud strategy does this teach?','Dependency on free tiers is risky. Organisations need exit strategies, data portability plans, and should budget for potential costs even when using free tiers.',1),
-- (656,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An election result in Ghana is disputed. The Electoral Commission has Big Data from voting machines. Analyse how this data could be used and misused.','Used correctly: independent verification of counts. Misused: selective data release to support preferred outcomes, manipulation of machine data, or using data to intimidate voters.',1),
-- (657,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian port uses autonomous cranes to load and unload ships. Human crane operators are retrained as crane supervisors. Analyse this transition model.','Supervised automation is a positive transition model — workers gain new skills, maintain employment, and provide the human oversight needed for safe autonomous operations.',1),
-- (658,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian teenager uses cryptocurrency to receive payment for online freelance work. Their parents confiscate their earnings. Analyse the digital financial rights issue.','Children\'s right to earnings from their own labour intersects with parental authority — digital financial tools give young people financial autonomy that raises complex family and legal questions.',1),
-- (659,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AR app allows users to virtually redecorate their homes before painting. It collects detailed 3D scans of home interiors. Analyse the privacy risk.','Interior 3D scans reveal home layout, security vulnerabilities, and valuable items — this data could be used for burglary planning if the company is breached or sold.',1),
-- (660,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana\'s government deploys an AI chatbot to handle citizen complaints. The chatbot frequently misunderstands complaints in Twi and gives wrong information. Analyse the failure.','The chatbot was not trained on Ghanaian languages and contexts. Critical government services must not be deployed without comprehensive local language and context testing.',1),
-- (661,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A smart school in Accra tracks student location, facial expressions, and keystroke patterns. Analyse whether this data collection is proportionate.','Tracking facial expressions and keystroke patterns goes far beyond safety needs — this is disproportionate surveillance that violates student dignity and privacy rights.',1),
-- (662,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian developer builds an app that becomes popular globally. They use cloud auto-scaling. Their monthly cloud bill goes from GHS 200 to GHS 200,000. Analyse the financial risk.','Viral growth without cost caps and alerts can cause unmanageable cloud bills. Developers must set spending alerts, implement rate limiting, and plan monetisation before going viral.',1),
-- (663,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana Statistical Service conducts a census using mobile phone location data instead of door-to-door enumeration. What populations would be undercounted?','Those without phones, phone registration, or living in low-signal areas — typically the poorest, most rural, and most vulnerable — would be systematically undercounted.',1),
-- (664,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian startup creates a blockchain solution for the fishing industry to track catches from sea to market. Analyse the stakeholder challenges in implementation.','Fishermen need smartphones, data connectivity at sea, and training. Processors need system integration. Buyers need trust in the data. Government needs regulatory framework.',1),
-- (665,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse how a Ghanaian maker space could use 3D printing to support local entrepreneurship in three specific sectors.','Agriculture: custom irrigation fittings. Healthcare: affordable prosthetics. Fashion: unique accessories. The maker space reduces production barriers for micro-entrepreneurs.',1),
-- (666,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian university wants to enter the FIRST Robotics Competition. Analyse the resources, skills, and support they need.','Requirements: engineering faculty mentors, electronics and programming skills, workshop space, component budget (GHS 20,000+), team collaboration skills, and competition travel funding.',1),
-- (667,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse the role of USSD in making fintech accessible to Ghanaians with feature phones (non-smartphones).','USSD (*170# etc.) works on any mobile phone without internet — crucial for the 40%+ of Ghanaians using feature phones, ensuring fintech inclusion regardless of smartphone access.',1),
-- (668,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A VR simulation of Accra\'s traffic helps urban planners test road design changes before implementation. Analyse the value of this simulation approach.','Virtual simulation reduces risk and cost of real-world experiments, allows testing of multiple scenarios, and identifies unintended consequences before expensive physical changes are made.',1),
-- (669,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse why AI assistants like ChatGPT perform worse when responding to questions about Ghanaian politics, culture, and current events.','AI is trained primarily on English internet data skewed toward Western content — Ghanaian-specific knowledge is underrepresented, causing hallucinations and inaccuracies.',1),
-- (670,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian village uses an IoT well-monitoring system. The system correctly alerts that the well is empty, but no one is trained to act on the alert. What systemic failure occurred?','Technology without training and response protocols is ineffective. IoT systems must be accompanied by trained human operators and clear action plans for each alert type.',1),
-- (671,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse the environmental impact of cloud computing, especially for Ghana which generates electricity partly from hydropower.','Cloud computing consumes massive electricity globally. If Ghana\'s cloud data centres run on renewable hydropower, the carbon impact is lower than fossil-fuel-powered alternatives.',1),
-- (672,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian supermarket chain uses loyalty card data to identify which customers are pregnant before they announce it, enabling targeted marketing. Analyse the ethical issue.','Inferring sensitive personal conditions (pregnancy) from purchasing data without explicit consent violates privacy expectations and can cause real harm if wrong or unwanted.',1),
-- (673,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana\'s government wants to put all public contracts on a blockchain. Contractors resist transparency. Analyse both sides of this debate.','Government: blockchain prevents corruption, ensures accountability, and builds public trust. Contractors: fear exposure of commercially sensitive bid information and competitive disadvantage.',1),
-- (674,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian school uses 3D printing but the teacher has no training. Students teach themselves from YouTube. Analyse the learning outcomes of this approach.','Peer and self-directed learning builds resilience, problem-solving, and digital literacy — but without teacher guidance, safety risks and misuse of equipment may occur.',1),
-- (675,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian farmer uses a robot to apply pesticides precisely only where needed. Analyse the environmental and economic benefit versus traditional spraying.','Precision application reduces chemical use by up to 90%, lowering costs, reducing soil contamination, protecting beneficial insects, and improving food safety.',1),
-- (676,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse how real-time gross settlement (RTGS) via GhIPSS differs from traditional bank transfers in Ghana.','RTGS settles transactions immediately and individually in real time. Traditional transfers may take hours or days to clear. RTGS reduces settlement risk for large transactions.',1),
-- (677,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A funeral home in Accra offers VR experiences where families can "visit" with deceased relatives through AI-generated avatars. Analyse the psychological and ethical concerns.','While offering comfort, AI resurrection of the dead may interfere with healthy grieving, create unrealistic expectations, and raise questions about consent of the deceased.',1),
-- (678,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI reads chest X-rays in a rural Ghanaian clinic where no radiologist is available. The AI recommends treatment. The recommendation is wrong. Who is responsible?','The clinic deploying the AI, the AI developer, and the treating clinician share responsibility. Clear liability frameworks for AI medical tools in resource-limited settings are urgently needed.',1),
-- (679,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian market association creates a community blockchain to track member contributions and distribute profits. What governance structure should they create?','The association needs clear rules for: who validates transactions, how disputes are resolved, how the code can be updated, and what happens if a member leaves.',1),
-- (680,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse the potential of 3D-printed housing to address Ghana\'s one million unit housing deficit.','3D printing can print basic structures faster and cheaper than traditional methods. Challenges: material supply, regulatory approval, skilled operators, and social acceptance of printed homes.',1),
-- (681,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse how IoT could transform Ghanaian traditional medicine by tracking herb supply chains and quality.','IoT sensors on herb supplies could track temperature, humidity, and location — ensuring quality and authenticity from farm to practitioner, preventing adulteration.',1),
-- (682,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A government agency uses AI in the cloud to screen visa applications. The AI rejects all applications from a specific Ghanaian ethnic group at higher rates. Who must act and how?','The agency must immediately suspend the AI, conduct an independent audit, review all rejected applications, and implement bias testing before redeployment.',1),
-- (683,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse three ways Ghana\'s education system could use Big Data to improve learning outcomes.','1. Track student performance to identify struggling students early. 2. Optimise school resource allocation. 3. Analyse which teaching methods produce the best exam outcomes by subject.',1),
-- (684,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian NGO deploys robots to clear landmines in conflict-affected areas. Analyse why this is one of the most beneficial applications of robotics.','Landmine clearance robots eliminate the risk to human deminers, can work faster, and can access areas too dangerous for humans — saving lives directly.',1),
-- (685,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana\'s Cybersecurity Act 2020 (Act 1038) creates the Cybersecurity Authority. Analyse its importance for the fintech sector.','The Cybersecurity Authority sets standards for digital security, can investigate breaches, and enforces compliance — protecting fintech users from fraud, data theft, and cyber attacks.',1),
-- (686,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse whether VR therapy (for PTSD, phobias) could be effectively delivered in Ghana given infrastructure and cultural barriers.','VR therapy requires headsets, trained therapists, and cultural adaptation of content. Infrastructure barriers include electricity and cost. Cultural barriers include stigma around mental health.',1),
-- (687,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI tutoring app in Ghana adapts lesson difficulty based on student responses. A student deliberately gives wrong answers to get easier questions. Analyse the design flaw.','The AI can be gamed — students who learn to manipulate the system get easier lessons without learning. The system needs anomaly detection and teacher visibility of behaviour.',1),
-- (688,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse whether blockchain voting could increase voter participation among Ghana\'s youth.','Blockchain mobile voting could increase youth participation by enabling voting from smartphones. Risks include digital literacy gaps, smartphone access inequality, and security concerns.',1),
-- (689,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian teacher uses 3D printing to create tactile learning materials for visually impaired students. Analyse the inclusive education impact.','3D-printed tactile maps, models, and diagrams transform abstract concepts into physical objects that visually impaired students can explore — significantly improving inclusion.',1),
-- (690,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse how IoT could help Ghana achieve its Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) related to clean water and sanitation.','IoT sensors monitor water quality, detect pipe leaks, track reservoir levels, and optimise distribution — directly supporting SDG 6 (Clean Water) and reducing waterborne disease.',1),
-- (691,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Cloud Computing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian research institution wants to run AI models requiring 1000 GPU hours of computation. Compare cloud versus on-premise options.','Cloud: pay-as-you-go GPU access within hours, no upfront cost, flexible. On-premise: high upfront cost (GHS 2M+), ongoing maintenance, but cheaper long-term for continuous heavy use.',1),
-- (692,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Big Data','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse how the 2021 Ghana census could have been enhanced using Big Data from multiple sources.','Combining traditional enumeration with mobile data, satellite imagery, and administrative records could improve accuracy, identify missed populations, and reduce cost.',1),
-- (693,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Robotics','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Ghana wants to develop a national robotics curriculum. Analyse what it should include for SHS students.','Curriculum should cover: basic electronics, programming (Python, block-based), mechanical design, AI concepts, ethics of automation, and hands-on build-and-test projects.',1),
-- (694,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse how AI-powered credit scoring using alternative data (MoMo history, social media) changes access to credit for Ghanaians without traditional credit history.','Alternative data unlocks credit for the financially excluded but raises fairness concerns — social media data may penalise people for personal beliefs rather than financial behaviour.',1),
-- (695,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','AR and VR','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian heritage site at Cape Coast Castle offers VR experiences of the slave trade dungeons. Analyse the memorial, educational, and commercial tensions.','VR memorialisation serves education and preservation but commercialisation of trauma risks exploitation. Revenue should support the site and affected communities.',1),
-- (696,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Artificial Intelligence','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An AI system is used to allocate NHIA (National Health Insurance) resources in Ghana. Patients in rural areas consistently receive less. Analyse the systemic cause.','The AI may be trained on historical allocation data that reflected geographic bias — urban areas received more resources historically, and the AI perpetuates this pattern.',1),
-- (697,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Blockchain','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'A Ghanaian university uses blockchain to issue and verify academic certificates globally. Five years later, the blockchain company shuts down. What happens to the certificates?','If the blockchain is truly decentralised, records persist. If it was a private company-controlled blockchain, records may be lost — illustrating why public blockchains are preferable for permanent records.',1),
-- (698,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','3D Printing','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse why Ghana\'s manufacturing sector should invest in 3D printing technology despite higher initial costs.','3D printing enables local production of custom parts, reduces import dependency, speeds product development, and positions Ghana\'s manufacturers for Industry 4.0 competitiveness.',1),
-- (699,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Internet of Things','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'An IoT-connected insulin pump in a Ghanaian diabetic patient is hacked and delivers a fatal dose. Analyse the security and legal implications.','Medical device hacking is a form of assault. Device manufacturers must implement cybersecurity by design. This case requires criminal investigation, civil liability, and regulatory reform.',1),
-- (700,1,1,'mcq','S1/SS2','Ghana Fintech','Analyse','Hard',1,1,'Analyse how Ghana can use its fintech leadership to position itself as Africa\'s digital payments hub.','Ghana can attract fintech headquarters through supportive regulation, sandbox programmes, GhIPSS API access, investor visas for tech founders, and positioning Accra as the African Silicon Valley.',1);

